	  	  	</tr>
	<tr bgcolor="#F2F2F2">
	  <td valign='top' bgcolor='#F2F2F2' glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'>_______</td>
	  <td valign='top' bgcolor='#F2F2F2' glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'>A. Ethernet frames do not have a time to live (TTL).</td>
  </tr>
	<tr bgcolor="#DDDDDD">
	  <td valign='top' glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'>_______</td>
	  <td valign='top' glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'>B. Broadcast frames are forwarded out all switch ports, except the originating port.</td>
  </tr>
	<tr bgcolor="#F2F2F2">
	  <td valign='top' bgcolor='#F2F2F2' glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'>_______</td>
	  <td valign='top' bgcolor='#F2F2F2' glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'>C. In a hierarchical design, redundancy is achieved at the distribution and core layers through additional hardware and alternate paths through the additional hardware.</td>
  </tr>
	<tr bgcolor="#DDDDDD">
	  <td valign='top' bgcolor="#DDDDDD" glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'>_______</td>
	  <td valign='top' bgcolor="#DDDDDD" glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'>D. Layer 2 loops result in low CPU load on all switches caught in the loop.</td>
  </tr>
	<tr bgcolor="#DDDDDD">
	  <td valign='top' bgcolor="#F2F2F2" glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'>_______</td>
	  <td valign='top' bgcolor="#F2F2F2" glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'>E. A broadcast storm results when there are so many broadcast frames caught in a Layer 2 loop that  all available bandwidth is consumed.</td>
  </tr>
	<tr bgcolor="#DDDDDD">
	  <td valign='top' bgcolor="#DDDDDD" glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'>_______</td>
	  <td valign='top' bgcolor="#DDDDDD" glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'>F. Most upper layer protocols are designed to recognize or cope with duplicate transmissions.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr bgcolor="#DDDDDD">
	  <td valign='top' bgcolor="#F2F2F2" glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'>_______</td>
	  <td valign='top' bgcolor="#F2F2F2" glow='false' glowcolor='#FCA92E' type='dynamic'>G. Layer 2 loops arise as a result of multiple paths, and STP can be used to block these loops.</td>
  </tr>
</table>]]></text>
</component>
